The <span style="color: #4A5C2A;">Bürgerblock</span> government has successfully implemented a nationwide ban on the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span>! [? if interior_minister == "Wirth": Interior Minister Wirth's determined leadership proved crucial in overcoming Conservative resistance?][? if stegerwald_prussia: Adam Stegerwald's influence in Prussia helped coordinate the crackdown?][? if judiciary_reformed: The reformed judiciary has proven more cooperative in enforcing the ban?].

The operation has dealt a significant blow to Nazi street power. Political violence has dropped noticeably, and the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span>'s intimidation tactics have been severely curtailed. However, the success comes at a cost - Conservative partners in the coalition are increasingly uncomfortable, and President Hindenburg has made his displeasure clear.

[? if player_choice_sa_ban == "federal": The aggressive approach has strained coalition unity, with some <span style="color: #C0A054;">DVP</span> and Conservative members questioning whether the cure is worse than the disease.?][? if player_choice_sa_ban == "consensus": The careful consensus-building approach helped maintain some coalition cohesion, though cracks are still visible.?]

General Schleicher and the Reichswehr leadership are furious, seeing this as interference with their plans to "tame" the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Nazis</span>. Rumors circulate that they are already planning countermeasures.

- @end: A costly victory.

