The <span style="color: #4A5C2A;">Bürgerblock</span> has managed to implement a nationwide <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span> ban, but the effort was marred by internal divisions and leaked information. Conservative resistance within the coalition ensured that the ban's enforcement would be half-hearted at best.

Many <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span> units received advance warning and moved their weapons to safety. The ban exists on paper, but the Nazi paramilitary infrastructure remains largely intact. Political violence has decreased only marginally.

[? if player_choice_sa_ban == "federal": The rushed approach created deep fissures within the coalition, with Conservative partners openly questioning the government's direction.?][? if player_choice_sa_ban == "consensus": Even the careful consensus-building couldn't overcome fundamental disagreements about how to handle the Nazi threat.?]

President Hindenburg is incensed, viewing this as both ineffective governance and an attack on Conservative interests. The <span style="color: #4A5C2A;">Bürgerblock's</span> days may be numbered.

- @end: A pyrrhic victory at best.

