The evidence of the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span> coup plot sits on Interior Minister's desk, but the government lacks the political will to act. This public display of weakness has only emboldened the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Nazis</span>, who now see the <span style="color: #4A5C2A;">Bürgerblock</span> as impotent.

[? if player_choice_sa_ban == "federal": The attempt to push through federal action without coalition support has exposed the government's internal contradictions.?][? if player_choice_sa_ban == "consensus": Even the search for consensus revealed irreconcilable differences within the coalition.?]

The <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span> and trade unions are furious, viewing this as a betrayal of democratic principles. Chancellor Brüning's position appears increasingly untenable as the coalition crumbles around him.

- @end: The writing is on the wall.

